                <head>242. Letter From the Under Secretary of State for Management (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RBH_1">Read</persName>) to the Director of the Office of
                    Government Employment, Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (Mathew)<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d242fn1">Source: National Archives, RG 59,
                        Records of the Under Secretary for Management (M), 1980, Box 3, Chron March
                        15–22, 1980. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1980-03-22">March 22, 1980</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Mathew:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Enclosed is the Department of State’s Supplemental Affirmative Action Plan for
                    the hiring, placement and advancement of handicapped individuals and disabled
                    veterans for Fiscal Year 1980.</p>
                <p>As requested, the Department of State will put special emphasis on the
                    recruitment and placement of persons with specified severe disabilities under
                    this Plan.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RBH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ben H. Read</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d242fn2">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RBH_1">Read</persName> signed “<persName
                                corresp="#p_RBH_1">Ben Read</persName>” above this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
